[{"id":"VH967036","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two sets of conducting spheres, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Figure 1 shows conducting sphere A, which has a radius of R. A note indicates that Q sub A equals Q. Conducting sphere B is near conducting sphere A, and has a radius of one half R. A note indicates that Q sub B equals Q. Figure 2 shows sphere A and sphere B connected by a wire.\" height=\"167\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH967036.g03.png\" width=\"600\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two conducting spheres are isolated from their surroundings. The radii of spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>R</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half R\"><math alttext=\"one half R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>R/2</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, respectively. Initially sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is neutral. A wire is connected between the sphere. Which of the following gives the final charge on each sphere after equilibrium is reached and provides a statement of reasoning to support this claim?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH967036_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub A equals Q and Q sub B equals 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub A equals Q and Q sub B equals 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because both spheres must create the same electric field at their surface.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub A equals the fraction Q over 2, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 2\"><math alttext=\"Q sub A equals the fraction Q over 2, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because both spheres must create the same electric field at their surface.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub A equals the fraction 2 Q over 3, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 3\"><math alttext=\"Q sub A equals the fraction 2 Q over 3, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because both spheres must create the same electric field at their surface.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub A equals the fraction Q over 2, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 2\"><math alttext=\"Q sub A equals the fraction Q over 2, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because both spheres must be at the same electric potential.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub A equals the fraction 2 Q over 3, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 3\"><math alttext=\"Q sub A equals the fraction 2 Q over 3, and Q sub B equals the fraction Q over 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because both spheres must be at the same electric potential.</p>"],"answer":4}]